<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="600" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• Small to medium-sized, long-tailed marsupials with short forelimbs and long hindlimbs, pelage mostly gray or brownish, often with some rufous tones.</paragraph>
<caption box="[1235,1424,891,924]" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="600" targetBox="[1461,1855,922,1112]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" box="[1235,1424,891,924]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• 55-83 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption box="[1235,1592,1128,1161]" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="600" targetBox="[220,1166,776,1400]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" box="[1235,1592,1128,1161]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• Australiasian Region.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• Forest and woodland with a dense understory of grass or shrubs, or dense heath and shrublands.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" box="[1235,1910,1246,1279]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• 3 genera, 8 species, at least 10 extant taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1233,2116,773,1367]" pageId="0" pageNumber="600">• 2 species Critically Endangered, 2 species Endangered; 2 subspecies and 2 species Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
